  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2020-06-11",
    "date": "2022-06-01T15:02:17Z",
    "text": "Mandatory Minimum Reform Act of 2020\n\nThis bill eliminates most mandatory minimum prison terms for drug offenses involving the import, export, manufacture, distribution, or possession with intent to distribute a controlled substance.\n\nAdditionally, it eliminates mandatory minimum prison terms for the following drug offenses:\n\n simple possession, distribution to an individual under age 21 by an individual at least age 18, distribution or manufacture in a school zone, and use of an individual under age 18 to distribute. Finally, the bill requires prior written approval of the Attorney General to prosecute a defendant for certain drug offenses that involve low-level drug quantities (e.g., less than one kilogram of heroin or less than 500 grams of cocaine-based substances)."
  },
